
[1]conceivable

   CONCEIVABLE, a. [See Conceive.]

   1. That may be imagined, or thought; capable of being framed in the
   mind by the fancy or imagination.

   If it were possible to contrive an invention, whereby any conceivable
   weight may be moved by any conceivable power.

   2. That may be understood or believed.

   It is not conceivable, that it should be the very person, whose shape
   and voice it assumed.
